# deepagent (project overlay)

Global policy: `~/.cursor/rules/claude-code-sync.mdc` and `~/.claude/CLAUDE.md` (from `~/claude-agent-instructions/`). Do **not** duplicate the coordination cycle, skills, or git workflow here.

## Project memory

Project-specific runbooks live in `~/arcadia/robot/deepagent/.claude/agent-memory/MEMORY.md` (+ leaves). Read the index before launching pipelines, retesting, or interpreting numbers/TTL from a ticket.

The directory is symlinked from `~/.claude/projects/<cwd-hash>/memory/` by `~/claude-agent-instructions/scripts/setup-project-memory.sh`, so writes through the native auto-memory mechanism land in the project tree and are versioned in the project's git.

## Tool permissions

`.cursor/cli.json` mirrors `.claude/settings.local.json` in this repository. Keep them aligned — drift breaks Cursor's permission prompts.

## Where to edit instructions

- **Global** agent rules → `~/claude-agent-instructions/` (`CLAUDE.md`, `agents/`, `skills/`, `cursor-rules/`).
- **deepagent project** runbooks → `~/arcadia/robot/deepagent/.claude/agent-memory/` (commit to project git).
- **This overlay** — only deepagent-specific gates that cannot live in either of the above.
